President Obama will embark on a three-day economic bus tour in the Midwest from August 15-17. He will make stops in southern Minnesota, northeastern Iowa, and western Illinois to discuss strategies for growing the economy, strengthening the middle class, and promoting hiring. The President aims to engage with Americans, including local families and small business owners, to hear their perspectives. He believes it is crucial to promote economic growth, restore confidence in the nation's future, and foster optimism for future generations.